00053 /**
00054  * \ingroup Sierra
00055  * \brief Container for Sierra function information
00056  * 
00057  * \description
00058  *
00059  *   This struct holds information specific to Sierra functions.
00060  *   The abscissa (x) and ordinate (y) labels are optional and default
00061  *   values are "" (empty string). The function values are stored
00062  *   in a single array as 'xyxyxyxy...'. Minimum and maximum values
00063  *   of the abscissa and ordinate are also provided. Note that
00064  *   a function can have a single value, in which case the values
00065  *   of the min and max ordinate are undefined.
00066  *
00067  * \modifications
00068  *   - 2003-JUN-24  W Koegler  Created.
00069  *   - 2003-SEP-03  W Koegler  Expanded to support all function variables.
00070  */
00071 typedef struct {
00072   // From the Sierra input deck
00073   char name[100];   /**< name of the function */
00074   char type[100];   /**< type is either 'constant' or 'piecewise linear' */
00075   char abscissa_label[100]; /**< optional label for abscissa (default = "") */
00076   char ordinate_label[100]; /**< optional label for abscissa (default = "") */
00077   int numValue;  /**< function has either 1 or an even number of values */
00078   double* values; /**< values are stored in array ordered as 'xyxyxy...' */
00079   // Calculated values
00080   double abscissa_min;  /**< minimum value of the abscissa (x min) */
00081   double ordinate_min;  /**< minimum value of the ordinate (y min) */
00082   double abscissa_max;  /**< maximum value of the abscissa (x max) */
00083   double ordinate_max;  /**< maximum value of the ordinate (y max) */
00084 } FC_SierraFuncInfo;
00085 
00086 /**
00087  * \ingroup  Sierra
00088  * \brief Container for Sierra spot weld information
00089  * 
00090  * \description
00091  *
00092  *   This struct holds information specific to Sierra spot welds.
00093  *   Indices into the owning FC_SierraInfo struct's function list
00094  *   are also provided for the normal and tangential functions.
00095  *   (E.g. given FC_SierraInfo sierra, the normal function of the
00096  *   ith spotweld can be found as 
00097  *   sierra->functions[sierra->spotwelds[i]->normalId].)
00098  *
00099  * \modifications
00100  *   - 2003-JUN-24  W Koegler  Created.
00101  *   - 2003-SEP-02  W Koegler  Added all possible spot weld variables.
00102  *   - 2007-OCT-15 ACG removed refs to saf.
00103  */
00104 typedef struct {
00105   // From the Sierra input deck
00106   char name[100];    /**< name of the spot weld */
00107   char nodeset[100]; /**< name of node set (welded to the surface) */
00108   char surface[100]; /**< name of surface (welded to the node set) */
00109   char normal[100];  /**< name of normal displacement function */
00110   char tangent[100]; /**< name of tangential displacement function */
00111   double normal_scale; /**< scale factor for normal displacement function */ 
00112   double tangent_scale; /**< scale factor for tangential displacement function */ 
00113   double exponent;    /**< value of the failure envelope exponent */
00114   int decay_cycles;  /**< number of failure decay cycles */
00115   // Computed after parsing to make access easier
00116   int normalId;  /**< index of the normal function in SierraInfo function list */
00117   FC_SierraFuncInfo* normal_p; /**< pointer to normal function */
00118   int tangentId; /**< index of tangential function in SierraInfo function list */
00119   FC_SierraFuncInfo* tangent_p; /**< pointer to normal function */
00120   char nodeset_name[100]; /**< nodeset name */ 
00121   char surface_name[100]; /**< surface name */ 
00122 } FC_SierraSpotWeldInfo;
00123 
00124 /**
00125  * \ingroup  Sierra
00126  * \brief Container for Sierra information
00127  * 
00128  * \description
00129  *
00130  *   This struct holds information found in a Sierra input file.
00131  *   Sierra is a framework that provides management of a variety of
00132  *   physics simulation codes and their data. The input file contains
00133  *   instructions to perform a simulation.
00134  *
00135  *   Currently, the SierraInfo struct holds only the information needed 
00136  *   to analyze Presto spot welds. This includes the name of the
00137  *   the Sierra problem, alias for the result variables "displacement"
00138  *   and "force_external", the number of functions and pointers to
00139  *   FC_SierraFunctionInfo structs, and the number of spots welds
00140  *   and pointers to FC_SpotWeldInfo structs.
00141  *
00142  *   Basic handling routines (init, clear, print) are provided only
00143  *   for the SierraInfo struct, and not its subelements as they
00144  *   (the subelements) are not expected to be handled independently
00145  *   of the SierraInfo struct. 
00146  *
00147  *   Knowledge of this struct and it's member structs is necessary to
00148  *   access the contained data.
00149  *
00150  * \modifications
00151  *   - 2003-JUN-24  W Koegler Created.
00152  *
00153  * \todo
00154  *   Instead of a name for each results variable, keep a list
00155  *   of variable/alias pairs. Also, keep track of type of variable
00156  *   i.e. node, element, or global.
00157  */
00158 typedef struct {
00159   char name[100];  /**< name of the sierra problem */
00160   char displ_alias[100];  /**< alias of the displacement variable */
00161   char f_ext_alias[100];  /**< alias of the force_external variable */
00162   int numFunction;        /**< number of functions */
00163   FC_SierraFuncInfo** functions; /**< array of pointers to functions */
00164   int numSpotWeld;        /**< number of spot welds */
00165   FC_SierraSpotWeldInfo** spotwelds; /**< array of pointers to spot welds */
00166 } FC_SierraInfo;
